Meet Bhumicka Singh, the Bollywood Queen of Goa! 🌟 

From transforming Goa’s nightlife with Bollywood beats to becoming a hospitality influencer, her journey from Bollywood to Goa’s nightlife is nothing short of inspiring. 

A big shoutout to her amazing team and supporters! 👏✨

 #BollywoodInGoa 

[ Bollywood, Goa nightlife, Bollywood music
Club Titos, Bollywood Queen, Nightlife, Hospitality awards, Goa clubs, Influencer success ]

AND THIS HAPPENED- IHC - International Hospitality Council london & IIHM goa honours me with The Hospitality Influencer Of The Year Award 2024 🫶🏻✨❤️
A bit about my journey 
My love affair with goa begun ever since I can remember from celebrating birthdays to spending new years - In 2015 I met @ricardotitosgoa and as we chatted we came up with an idea and curated Bollywood sundowner with Bhumicka singh at Titos ,a bollywood night hosted by me with a bunch of talented DJs -a night for Bollywood music lovers in a Techno driven goa where bollywood was loooked down upon and DJs refused to play bollywood . That was the turning point of Goan nightlife and the Introduction of Bollywoid music which made way for more tourism and attracting party lovers to our Bollywood nights in Titos all over India and abroad - hence the nickname Bollywood queen of goa which till today has thousands of people partying at my event every Friday Saturday with me and my DJs @djmackvieira  and @krissmusiccc . That was the steppingstone of my journey in the hospitality industry . Today as you all know Goa is the hub for many bollywood artists and DJs . Along the way I made great friends in the hospitality industry  who hosted me fed me ☺️and I associated with well known names and actively promoted hotels , resorts , fashion , lifestyle in goa as in influencer .They trusted me with their vision to promote 😃
I have been forever grateful to play a small part and contribute to the hospitality industry and promote Goa tourism via my social media in my own way . Goa is second home and there is so much more I would like to do for the city who has given me so much 🙏Thank you the handful ones who supported me ✨🫶🏻

latestPosts.caption:
Dear Citizens of India,

While our Indian Army and Navy forces are protecting the country, with  civilians being asked to evacuate their homes around border areas, stray animals are also impacted during such tough times.

If you your family and friends live around that area, then request you to kindly keep a check on the stray animals around and provide them with food, water and shelter as much as you can do at your end.

In case of emergency, or any medical assistance that a stray animal would need and gets injured, then please reach out to us and DM with location and details for the injured animal, we will try our best to mobilise team from animal welfare services and get them best possible help, even if that means sending an animal ambulance to that area.

We are here to support you and will always stand for voiceless souls too who cannot fight for themselves.

Jai Hind 🫡🇮🇳
